definition.value: A retinol in which all four exocyclic double bonds have E- (trans-) geometry.
A CDP-sugar having 3,6-dideoxy-D-glucose as the sugar component.
An organic sulfide that is hydrogen sulfide substituted by two prop-1-en-1-yl groups. It is a volatile constituent found in garlic and onions.
An L-ornithine compound having an acyl substituent at the N(5)-position.
